  "prompt": "Is the scheme of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in most countries around the world. It is a criminal offense that involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other criminal enterprises) appear to be legally earned. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate\n\nMoney laundering is a serious crime that can result in significant legal penalties, including:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nMost countries have strict anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to detect and prevent such activities.",
